            "type": "text",
            "text": "Caching"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Caching is the highest-leverage inference optimisation available to most LLMOps teams: a cache hit eliminates the entire LLM call, saving both latency and cost. Three distinct caching layers apply at different granularities \u2014 exact-match response caching, semantic caching, and provider-side KV (prompt) caching. Each layer covers a different class of repeated workload and can be stacked."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
