          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Three-tier LLM caching hierarchy: L1 exact-match response cache (Redis), L2 semantic cache (vector store), L3 provider KV cache (prompt caching). Requests cascade through layers; a hit at any layer avoids the LLM API call."
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Each layer has a different trade-off between implementation complexity, hit rate, and the correctness of the cached response:"
          }
