        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "L1: Exact-Match Response Cache"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The simplest cache: compute a hash of the exact inputs (model, messages, temperature, max_tokens) and store the response. On an identical request, return the cached response without calling the LLM. Correct by definition \u2014 if the inputs are identical, the response is interchangeable (for temperature=0)."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Implementation"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import hashlib, json, time\nimport redis.asyncio as aioredis\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel\n\nredis_client = aioredis.Redis(host=\"localhost\", port=6379)\n\nclass ChatRequest(BaseModel):\n    model: str\n    messages: list[dict]\n    temperature: float = 0.0\n    max_tokens: int = 1024\n\ndef _cache_key(req: ChatRequest) -> str | None:\n    # Only cache deterministic (temperature=0) requests\n    if req.temperature != 0.0:\n        return None\n    payload = json.dumps(\n        {\n            \"model\": req.model,\n            \"messages\": req.messages,\n            \"temperature\": req.temperature,\n            \"max_tokens\": req.max_tokens,\n        },\n        sort_keys=True,\n    )\n    return \"llm:exact:\" + hashlib.sha256(payload.encode()).hexdigest()\n\nasync def cached_llm_call(req: ChatRequest, llm_fn, ttl: int = 3600) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Call LLM with exact-match caching; returns cached result if available.\"\"\"\n    key = _cache_key(req)\n\n    if key:\n        cached = await redis_client.get(key)\n        if cached:\n            result = json.loads(cached)\n            result[\"cache_hit\"] = \"exact\"\n            return result\n\n    result = await llm_fn(req)\n    result[\"cache_hit\"] = None\n\n    if key:\n        await redis_client.setex(key, ttl, json.dumps(result))\n\n    return result"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Never cache temperature > 0 responses. The caller expects stochastic output; returning the same cached response eliminates the diversity temperature is meant to produce and can create subtle correctness bugs."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "L2: Semantic Cache"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Semantic caching extends exact-match to near-identical queries: embed the incoming query, search a vector index of previously-answered queries, and return the cached response if a sufficiently similar query was answered before. This catches paraphrases, typo variants, and equivalent phrasings that differ in wording but not meaning."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Implementation with Qdrant"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from qdrant_client import QdrantClient\nfrom qdrant_client.models import Distance, VectorParams, PointStruct, Filter, FieldCondition, Range\nfrom openai import AsyncOpenAI\nimport hashlib, time, uuid\n\nqdrant = QdrantClient(host=\"localhost\", port=6333)\nopenai_client = AsyncOpenAI()\n\nSEMANTIC_CACHE_COLLECTION = \"llm_semantic_cache\"\nSIMILARITY_THRESHOLD = 0.95   # cosine; tune per use case\nCACHE_TTL_SECONDS = 1800      # 30 minutes\n\nasync def get_query_embedding(query: str) -> list[float]:\n    resp = await openai_client.embeddings.create(\n        model=\"text-embedding-3-small\",\n        input=query,\n    )\n    return resp.data[0].embedding\n\nasync def semantic_cache_lookup(\n    query: str,\n    model: str,\n) -> dict | None:\n    \"\"\"Return cached response if a semantically similar query exists; else None.\"\"\"\n    embedding = await get_query_embedding(query)\n    now = time.time()\n\n    results = qdrant.search(\n        collection_name=SEMANTIC_CACHE_COLLECTION,\n        query_vector=embedding,\n        limit=1,\n        score_threshold=SIMILARITY_THRESHOLD,\n        query_filter=Filter(\n            must=[\n                FieldCondition(key=\"model\", match={\"value\": model}),\n                FieldCondition(key=\"expires_at\", range=Range(gte=now)),\n            ]\n        ),\n        with_payload=True,\n    )\n\n    if results:\n        hit = results[0]\n        return {\"response\": hit.payload[\"response\"], \"cache_hit\": \"semantic\",\n                \"similarity\": hit.score}\n    return None\n\n\nasync def semantic_cache_store(query: str, model: str, response: str) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Store a query+response in the semantic cache.\"\"\"\n    embedding = await get_query_embedding(query)\n    qdrant.upsert(\n        collection_name=SEMANTIC_CACHE_COLLECTION,\n        points=[PointStruct(\n            id=str(uuid.uuid4()),\n            vector=embedding,\n            payload={\n                \"query\": query,\n                \"model\": model,\n                \"response\": response,\n                \"expires_at\": time.time() + CACHE_TTL_SECONDS,\n            },\n        )],\n    )"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Setting the similarity threshold"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The threshold is the most sensitive parameter in semantic caching. Too high (>0.98) and the cache rarely hits; too low (<0.90) and semantically different questions return wrong cached answers. Calibrate by measuring:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def evaluate_threshold(\n    test_pairs: list[tuple[str, str, bool]],\n    embeddings: dict[str, list[float]],\n    threshold: float,\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"\n    test_pairs: (query_a, query_b, should_match) \u2014 human-labelled pairs.\n    Returns precision and recall at the given threshold.\n    \"\"\"\n    import numpy as np\n\n    def cosine(a, b):\n        a, b = np.array(a), np.array(b)\n        return float(np.dot(a, b) / (np.linalg.norm(a) * np.linalg.norm(b)))\n\n    tp = fp = fn = tn = 0\n    for q_a, q_b, expected in test_pairs:\n        sim = cosine(embeddings[q_a], embeddings[q_b])\n        predicted = sim >= threshold\n        if predicted and expected:     tp += 1\n        elif predicted and not expected: fp += 1\n        elif not predicted and expected: fn += 1\n        else:                           tn += 1\n\n    precision = tp / (tp + fp) if (tp + fp) else 0\n    recall = tp / (tp + fn) if (tp + fn) else 0\n    return {\"threshold\": threshold, \"precision\": precision, \"recall\": recall,\n            \"tp\": tp, \"fp\": fp, \"fn\": fn, \"tn\": tn}\n\n# Sweep thresholds to find the best operating point\nfor t in [0.88, 0.90, 0.92, 0.95, 0.97, 0.99]:\n    print(evaluate_threshold(test_pairs, embeddings, t))"
          }
        ]
      },
