        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Anthropic explicit prompt caching"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\n# Place cache_control breakpoints at the end of stable prefix sections.\n# The prefix up to each breakpoint is cached and reused across requests.\n\nSYSTEM_PROMPT = \"\"\"You are a legal research assistant with expertise in EU competition law.\n[...10,000-word legal corpus here...]\"\"\"\n\ndef ask_legal_question(question: str) -> str:\n    response = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        max_tokens=1024,\n        system=[\n            {\n                \"type\": \"text\",\n                \"text\": SYSTEM_PROMPT,\n                \"cache_control\": {\"type\": \"ephemeral\"},  # cache this large prefix\n            }\n        ],\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": question}],\n    )\n    usage = response.usage\n    print(\n        f\"Input tokens: {usage.input_tokens} \"\n        f\"(cache_read={usage.cache_read_input_tokens} \"\n        f\"cache_write={usage.cache_creation_input_tokens})\"\n    )\n    return response.content[0].text\n\n# First call: cache_write = 10k tokens (full cost)\n# Subsequent calls: cache_read = 10k tokens (90% discount)\nanswer = ask_legal_question(\"Does excessive pricing constitute an abuse of dominance under Article 102?\")"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Designing prompts to maximise cache hits"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Place stable content first: system prompt, knowledge base context, few-shot examples. Place variable content last: the user's question, session-specific context."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "The cache key is the exact token sequence \u2014 even a single character change before the breakpoint invalidates the cache for everything after it."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "For RAG: if the system prompt is stable but the retrieved chunks change per query, put the system prompt under a cache breakpoint and the chunks after it (not cached). This saves prefill on the system prompt tokens."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "For multi-turn conversations: if the conversation grows token by token, the cache hit rate drops because each turn extends the prefix. Consider summarising older turns and placing a cache breakpoint after the stable system prompt."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Cache Invalidation"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Cached LLM responses become stale when:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Model version changes: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "A cached response from gpt-4o-2024-08-06 may differ from gpt-4o-2024-11-20. Include the model version in the cache key, or flush on model rollout."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Knowledge base updates: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "RAG-augmented responses embed retrieved chunks. If the document corpus changes, the cached answer may reference outdated content. Use a corpus version tag in the cache key or set a short TTL."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "System prompt changes: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Any change to the system prompt can alter outputs for the same user query. Bump a cache namespace version when deploying prompt changes."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Time-sensitive content: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Answers about current events, prices, or availability become stale fast. Use a TTL matched to the content's natural update frequency."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Namespace versioning for prompt deployments"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import hashlib, json\n\nPROMPT_VERSION = \"v3\"   # bump this whenever the system prompt changes\n\ndef versioned_cache_key(req: ChatRequest) -> str | None:\n    if req.temperature != 0.0:\n        return None\n    payload = json.dumps(\n        {\n            \"prompt_version\": PROMPT_VERSION,\n            \"model\": req.model,\n            \"messages\": req.messages,\n        },\n        sort_keys=True,\n    )\n    return \"llm:v:\" + hashlib.sha256(payload.encode()).hexdigest()"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Measuring Cache Effectiveness"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom typing import Literal\n\n@dataclass\nclass CacheMetrics:\n    exact_hits: int = 0\n    semantic_hits: int = 0\n    misses: int = 0\n    total_tokens_saved: int = 0\n    total_cost_saved_usd: float = 0.0\n\n    @property\n    def total_requests(self) -> int:\n        return self.exact_hits + self.semantic_hits + self.misses\n\n    @property\n    def hit_rate(self) -> float:\n        if self.total_requests == 0:\n            return 0.0\n        return (self.exact_hits + self.semantic_hits) / self.total_requests\n\n    def record(\n        self,\n        cache_layer: Literal[\"exact\", \"semantic\", None],\n        tokens_saved: int = 0,\n        cost_saved: float = 0.0,\n    ) -> None:\n        if cache_layer == \"exact\":\n            self.exact_hits += 1\n        elif cache_layer == \"semantic\":\n            self.semantic_hits += 1\n        else:\n            self.misses += 1\n        self.total_tokens_saved += tokens_saved\n        self.total_cost_saved_usd += cost_saved\n\n    def report(self) -> str:\n        return (\n            f\"Hit rate: {self.hit_rate:.1%} \"\n            f\"(exact={self.exact_hits}, semantic={self.semantic_hits}, \"\n            f\"miss={self.misses}) | \"\n            f\"Tokens saved: {self.total_tokens_saved:,} | \"\n            f\"Cost saved: ${self.total_cost_saved_usd:.2f}\"\n        )\n\nmetrics = CacheMetrics()"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LLM response caching operates at three layers: L1 exact-match (hash of inputs \u2192 full response in Redis, correct for temperature=0, 5\u201330% hit rate), L2 semantic caching (embedding similarity in a vector store, 10\u201340% hit rate, requires careful threshold calibration), and L3 provider KV/prompt caching (automatic for OpenAI, explicit breakpoints for Anthropic, 50\u201390% discount on repeated prompt prefixes). The three layers are complementary: L1 and L2 eliminate the API call entirely; L3 reduces the cost of calls that do reach the provider. Cache invalidation is the main operational hazard \u2014 include model version, prompt version, and corpus version in cache keys, and set TTLs matched to content update frequency."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
